# Function to remove outliers using the interquartile range (IQR)
def remove_outliers(df_tracks, column, threshold=1.5):
    q1 = df_tracks['popularity'].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = df_tracks['popularity'].quantile(0.75)
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lower_bound = q1 - threshold * iqr
    upper_bound = q3 + threshold * iqr
    df_no_outliers_1 = df_tracks[(df_tracks['popularity'] >= lower_bound) & (df_tracks['popularity'] <= upper_bound)]
    return df_no_outliers_1

# Apply the function to remove outliers from column 'popularity'
df_no_outliers_1= remove_outliers(df_tracks, 'popularity')
# Display the DataFrame without outliers
print(df_no_outliers_1)
